🔍 Key Insights
Students with high screen time (>4 hours) tend to have lower test scores compared to others.

Students with moderate screen time (2–4 hours) show relatively balanced performance.

Extracurricular activities do not negatively impact performance when maintained at moderate levels.

Students aged 16–17 show slightly better academic performance compared to other age groups.

💡 Recommendations
Limit screen time to less than 4 hours per day

Encourage a balance between study and extracurricular activities

Monitor students with low scores for early intervention

Promote structured study schedules

